text: Acleris paracinderella is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae. It is found in North America, where it has been recorded from California. The wingspan is 18–19 mm. Adults have been recorded on wing in February and from May to July.mothphotographersgroup The larvae feed on Prunus dumosa, Prunus fremontii, Prunus virginiana and Betula species.Tortricidae Food Plant Database ==References== Category:Moths described in 1964 paracinderella Category:Moths of North America
